accurate. it will be very helpful to provide the receiver's phone number with packages or expedite mails. the customs and delivery postmen usually need it. do not seal outgoing packages before taking them to the post office; they will not send them without inspecting the contents. generally it is best to buy the packing materials at the post office, and almost all post offices will pack your materials for you, at a reasonable price. most post offices and courier services will refuse to send cds or dvds, this can be circumvented by placing them in cd wallets along with lots 